{"id":"stage_retry_only_on_unexpectedmodelbehavior","type":"decision","fact":"The per-stage retry wrapper in `app/agents/lead.py` (controlled by `_STAGE_RETRIES = int(os.environ.get('STAGE_RETRIES','2'))`) retries ONLY on `UnexpectedModelBehavior`. `asyncio.TimeoutError`, `UsageLimitExceeded`, and the catch-all `Exception` branch all return `LimitedXFindings` on the first failure with no retry.","recommendation":"When adding new agent stages with retry behavior, mirror this four-branch except structure: (1) TimeoutError no-retry, (2) UnexpectedModelBehavior retried with `add_event('info', source, f'Retry {attempt+1}/{_STAGE_RETRIES}: {e}')` then `continue`, (3) UsageLimitExceeded no-retry with `add_event('agent_limit', ...)`, (4) Exception no-retry. Rationale: retrying on usage-limit or timeout does not change the underlying constraint; retrying on a generic Exception masks real bugs. Only validator-driven `UnexpectedModelBehavior` is genuinely transient.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"agent_pipeline_tdd_error_handling/iteration_02","date":"2026-05-24"}],"tags":["retries","error-handling","agents","lead-agent","stage-retry"],"affectedFiles":["app/agents/lead.py"],"createdAt":"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z"}
